<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-061-512  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 061 512.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  Jan 15 1990 v7 n3 p30(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Hospitals experiment with PC-to-PC image transfers. (CardinalGlennon Children's Hospital, University of Texas Health SciencesCenter)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Eckerson, Wayne.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Cardinal Glennon Children's Hospital of St. Louis, MO, isexperimenting on microcomputer-to-microcomputer transmission ofdigitized radiological images to the University of Texas HealthSciences Center in Houston, TX.andP;  The network will use switched56K-bps and ISDN services.andP;  If successful, the system will allowremote rural hospitals to avail of the expertise of specialistsand afford them the benefits of mainframe- or minicomputer-basedimaging systems that are otherwise too expensive.andP;  Medical images,such as X-rays, CAT scans, magnetic resonance images and medicalrecords, may be transmitted to experts in urban hospitals.andP;  Afterdiagnosing the images, the experts can consult with the doctors inremote hospitals by phone.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     HospitalMicrocomputersTestingImaging TechnologyTransmission LinesDigital VideoCardinal Glennon Children's HospitalUniversity of Texas Health Sciences CenterRecords ManagementHospital Information Systems.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>